        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 13 at 12:45PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 1245 PM CDT/145 PM EDT/, the public reported a cluster of strong
thunderstorms extending from Clifton to near Roselawn moving
southeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny to nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dunnington, Martinton, Thayer, Roselawn, Earl Park, Hanging Grove,
Brook, Foresman, Fair Oaks, Templeton, Morocco, Hopkins Park,
Beaverville, Oxford, Remington, Otterbein, Donovan, Boswell, Wadena,
Sumava Resorts, Swanington, Ambia, Baileys Corner, Mount Ayr, and
Goodland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
